description.narrative:
- Improved interest in and knowledge of the Council amongst journalists, especially from developing countries (and especially form Africa); 
- Improved awareness amongst journalists of their role as human rights defenders to hold governments accountable against the State’s human rights obligations and commitments;
- Increase in the number and quality of articles/broadcasts focused on the work and output of the Human Rights Council;
- Increase in the number of articles/broadcasts that seek to link debates and decisions at the Council, with ‘real world’ human rights issues and stories at national/local level.

